					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Have you looked in the source code of <em>Thwaite</em> to see how it does aiming? The <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">getAngle</tt> subroutine in <a href="https://github.com/pinobatch/thwaite-nes/blob/master/src/math.s" class="postlink">math.s</a> does the equivalent of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atan2" class="postlink">atan2</a> to find the approximate angle of a vector from (x1, y1) and (x2, y2). Then once you have the angle, you can use sine/cosine tables with one entry for each angle to set a bullet's velocity.<br /><br />A homing shot just repeats the aiming process for a bullet every 6 or 12 frames or whatever.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

