				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Having a table indexed by every possible delta X/Y combination is not really feasible, the table would be huge. Instead, we normally we use a table to translate <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">DeltaX divided by DeltaY</tt> (i.e. the ratio between the deltas) into an angle, which's a much smaller table. Divisions are slow on the 6502 though, and a common &quot;trick&quot; to speed this up is to use a log table and do a logarithmic division of the vales, which is just a subtraction, and use that result to lookup the angle in another table. You also need some extra logic to handle the different quadrants/octants.<br /><br />Here's an example of such a routine: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://codebase64.org/doku.php?id=base:8bit_atan2_8-bit_angle">http://codebase64.org/doku.php?id=base: ... -bit_angle</a><!-- m --></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
